  "text": "The scheduler binding decision reaches the kubelet through the following chain:\n\n## 1. Scheduler Binding Decision (pkg/scheduler/schedule_one.go:bindingCycle)\nThe scheduler's main scheduling cycle calls `bindingCycle()` which coordinates PreBind, Bind, and PostBind plugin phases. The Bind phase invokes binding plugins, with the default being the DefaultBinder.\n\n## 2. Scheduler Bind Plugin (pkg/scheduler/framework/plugins/defaultbinder/default_binder.go:Bind)\nThe DefaultBinder plugin's `Bind()` method creates a v1.Binding object containing the pod name, namespace, and target node name, then calls the Kubernetes API to create the binding via `CoreV1().Pods(binding.Namespace).Bind(ctx, binding, metav1.CreateOptions{})`.\n\n## 3. API Server Binding Handler (pkg/registry/core/pod/storage/storage.go:BindingREST)\nThe API server's BindingREST handler receives the binding request and implements the `Create()` method which:\n- Validates the binding object\n- Calls `setPodHostAndAnnotations()` to update the pod's spec.nodeName field\n- Updates pod status to PodScheduled condition\n- Persists the pod object to etcd with the node assignment\n\n## 4. Kubelet Pod Watch (pkg/kubelet/config/apiserver.go:NewSourceApiserver)\nThe kubelet runs `NewSourceApiserver()` which creates a list/watch client for pods assigned to the specific node (using field selector `spec.nodeName=<node-name>`). This watch detects when a pod's spec.nodeName is set, triggering pod updates to be sent to the kubelet's update channel.\n\n## 5. Kubelet Pod Sync Dispatch (pkg/kubelet/kubelet.go:HandlePodSyncs)\nWhen pod updates arrive, the kubelet's sync loop calls `HandlePodSyncs()` which dispatches each pod to the pod workers via `podWorkers.UpdatePod()` with SyncPodSync update type.\n\n## 6. Pod Admission Gates (pkg/kubelet/kubelet.go:canAdmitPod, pkg/kubelet/lifecycle/predicate.go:NewPredicateAdmitHandler)\nBefore a pod worker actually syncs the pod, the kubelet runs the pod through admission handlers via `canAdmitPod()`. The PredicateAdmitHandler evaluates whether a pod can be admitted by checking:\n- Container manager resource allocation\n- Critical pod admission handler (for evicting lower priority pods if needed)\n- Node conditions and capacity\n\nAdmission is checked in `pkg/kubelet/lifecycle/interfaces.go` via the `PodAdmitHandler` interface with `Admit()` method.\n\n## 7. Pod Worker Sync (pkg/kubelet/pod_workers.go:SyncPod)\nOnce admitted, the pod worker's `SyncPod()` interface is called with the pod and pod status. This is the podSyncer interface definition that coordinates the sync operation.\n\n## 8. Kubelet SyncPod Implementation (pkg/kubelet/kubelet.go:SyncPod)\nThe kubelet's `SyncPod()` implementation (around line 1844) is the main synchronization loop that:\n- Computes needed container changes\n- Creates/updates pod sandbox\n- Pulls container images\n- Creates and starts containers\n- Updates pod status in the status manager\n\nThis completes the path from scheduler binding decision to actual pod startup on the kubelet node."
}

